        <title>EPPO simple generic topic</title>

        <p> The <feature>EPPO simple</feature> generic topic serves many purposes and forms the base
            for several more-specialized topics.</p>

        <section>

            <title>Structure</title>

            <p> The <xml-element-name>generic-topic</xml-element-name> element is the top-level container for a
                <feature>generic topic</feature> XML  document. A valid generic topic document has
                the structure shown in the following <feature>structure diagram</feature>.</p>

            <fig href="../../../graphics/generic-topic.png">
                <title>EPPO simple generic-topic structure</title>
                <caption>
                    <p> The tag <code>&lt;generic-topic&gt;</code> labels the root element 
                        of a generic topic document.</p>
                </caption>
            </fig>

            <p> The <xml-element-name>head</xml-element-name> element holds the document
                <feature>header</feature>, which comprises the <feature>identity</feature> group, the
                revision <feature>history</feature> group, and the <feature>index</feature> group.
                The latter contains the set of terms discussed in the topic.  </p>

            <p> The <xml-element-name> body </xml-element-name> element holds the topic contents. A
                <feature> body content </feature> group follows the main <xml-element-name> title
            </xml-element-name> element and every section title.</p>

        </section>

